Invoicing ROI Simulator

A lightweight web app to calculate cost savings, ROI, and payback when switching from manual to automated invoicing. Built with React, Node.js/Express, and MongoDB. Supports scenario saving and report generation.

Features

Quick ROI simulation with key business inputs

Save, load, delete scenarios

Favorable cost-saving calculations

PDF/HTML report generation (email-gated)

Modern UI with light/dark mode toggle

Tech Stack

Frontend: React, CSS

Backend: Node.js, Express

Database: MongoDB

Hosting: Vercel (frontend), Render/Railway (backend)

Quick Start (Local)
# 1. Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/invoicing-roi-simulator.git
cd invoicing-roi-simulator

# 2. Backend
cd server
npm install
# Create .env with:
# MONGO_URI=<your_mongodb_connection_string>
# PORT=4000
npm start

# 3. Frontend
cd ../client
npm install
# Create .env with:
# REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:4000
npm start


Frontend runs at: http://localhost:3000

Backend runs at: http://localhost:4000

Deployment

Frontend: Vercel (client folder as root), set REACT_APP_API_URL to backend URL

Backend: Render or Railway, set MONGO_URI env var

API Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Purpose
POST	/simulate	Run ROI simulation
POST	/scenarios	Save scenario
GET	/scenarios	List scenarios
GET	/scenarios/:id	Get scenario
POST	/report/generate	Generate PDF/HTML report
Notes

.gitignore includes node_modules/ and .env

Dark mode subheadings are high-contrast for readability
